{
  "document_id": "job-21",
  "title": "Job 21",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-heading-job-replies:-the-wic",
      "type": "heading",
      "text": "Job Replies: The Wicked Often Go Unpunished"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "Then Job answered:"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "“Listen carefully to my words,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "Bear with me, and I will speak;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "As for me, is my complaint addressed to mortals?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "Look at me and be appalled,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "When I think of it I am dismayed,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "Why do the wicked live on,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "Their children are established in their presence"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "Their houses are safe from fear,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "Their bull breeds without fail;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "They send out their little ones like a flock,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "They sing to the tambourine and the lyre"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "They spend their days in prosperity,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "They say to God, ‘Leave us alone!"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "What is the Almighty, that we should serve him?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "Is not their prosperity indeed their own achievement?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "“How often is the lamp of the wicked put out?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "How often are they like straw before the wind"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "You say, ‘God stores up their iniquity for their children.’"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "Let their own eyes see their destruction,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "For what do they care for their household after them,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "Will any teach God knowledge,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "One dies in full prosperity,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "his loins full of milk"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "Another dies in bitterness of soul,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "They lie down alike in the dust,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "“Oh, I know your thoughts"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "For you say, ‘Where is the house of the prince?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "Have you not asked those who travel the roads,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "that the wicked are spared in the day of calamity"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-31",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 31,
      "text": "Who declares their way to their face,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-32",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 32,
      "text": "When they are carried to the grave,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-33",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 33,
      "text": "The clods of the valley are sweet to them;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-21-34",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 34,
      "text": "How then will you comfort me with empty nothings?"
    }
  ]
}